**README.md serves as the primary user-facing documentation entry point, providing installation workflows, command reference, configuration schema, and generated documentation structure for the agents-reverse-engineer CLI tool.**

## Installation Patterns

Interactive installer invoked via `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest` prompts for runtime selection (`claude`, `opencode`, `gemini`, `all`) and location (`-g` global or `-l` local). Non-interactive mode uses `--runtime <rt>` with `-g`/`-l` flags. Uninstallation via `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest uninstall` removes command files, session hooks, ARE permissions from `settings.json`, and `.agents-reverse-engineer` folder (local installs only). Version check via `--version` flag.

## Command Interface

CLI commands: `are install` (interactive or flagged), `are init` (creates `.agents-reverse-engineer/config.yaml`), `are discover` (scans files with `--plan` to generate `GENERATION-PLAN.md`, `--show-excluded` to display exclusion reasons), `are generate` (three-phase documentation generation), `are update` (incremental regeneration), `are specify` (synthesizes `specs/SPEC.md` with `--multi-file` split option and `--dry-run` preview), `are clean` (removes generated artifacts).

AI assistant skill commands: `/are-init`, `/are-discover`, `/are-generate`, `/are-update`, `/are-specify`, `/are-clean` available in Claude Code, OpenCode, and Gemini CLI runtimes.

## Configuration Schema

`.agents-reverse-engineer/config.yaml` structure:
- `exclude.patterns` (custom glob patterns like `["*.log", "temp/**"]`)
- `exclude.vendorDirs` (third-party directories: `node_modules`, `dist`, `.git`)
- `exclude.binaryExtensions` (file types: `.png`, `.jpg`, `.pdf`)
- `options.followSymlinks` (boolean, default `false`)
- `options.maxFileSize` (bytes, default `1048576` for 1MB)
- `output.colors` (boolean terminal ANSI flag)
- `output.verbose` (boolean per-file logging)
- `ai.backend` (enum: `'claude'`, `'gemini'`, `'opencode'`, `'auto'`)
- `ai.model` (string, backend-specific identifier like `sonnet`)
- `ai.timeoutMs` (number, default `300000` for 5-minute subprocess limit)
- `ai.maxRetries` (number, default `3` for exponential backoff)
- `ai.concurrency` (number 1-10, default `5`, reduced to `2` for WSL/resource-constrained environments)
- `ai.telemetry.keepRuns` (number, default `50` log retention count)
- `ai.telemetry.costThresholdUsd` (number, optional USD warning threshold)
- `ai.pricing.claude-opus-4.inputCostPerMTok` (USD per 1M input tokens, default `15.0`)
- `ai.pricing.claude-opus-4.outputCostPerMTok` (USD per 1M output tokens, default `75.0`)

## Generated Documentation Formats

`.sum` file structure includes YAML frontmatter with `file_type`, `generated_at` timestamp, followed by markdown sections: `## Purpose` (single-line role statement), `## Public Interface` (exported functions/classes with signatures), `## Dependencies` (library usage with purpose), `## Implementation Notes` (critical runtime behaviors).

`AGENTS.md` per-directory format includes directory role description, files grouped by purpose (Types, Services, Utils), subdirectories with brief descriptions.

Root documents: `CLAUDE.md` (auto-loaded Claude Code entry point), `GEMINI.md` (Gemini CLI entry point), `OPENCODE.md` (OpenCode entry point), `AGENTS.md` (universal format root directory overview).

## Workflow Sequence

Installation workflow: run `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest` → select runtime(s) → select location → installs commands and session hooks. Documentation generation workflow: run `/are-init` → `/are-discover` (creates `GENERATION-PLAN.md` with post-order traversal plan) → `/are-generate` (Phase 1: file analysis creates `.sum` files, Phase 2: directory docs creates `AGENTS.md`, Phase 3: root docs creates `CLAUDE.md`/`GEMINI.md`/`OPENCODE.md`) → `/are-update` (incremental regeneration for changed files only). Project specification synthesis via `/are-specify` aggregates all `AGENTS.md` into `specs/SPEC.md`.

## Requirements

Node.js 18+ runtime required. Supported AI assistants: Claude Code (full support with session hooks), Gemini CLI (full support with session hooks), OpenCode (AGENTS.md format supported), any assistant supporting `AGENTS.md` format.

